  "outputText": "Here's a thinking process:\n\n1.  **Understand User Query:**\n   - **Topic:** Local inference benchmarks for LLMs\n   - **Key Metrics Requested:** Prompt prefill throughput, decode throughput, time to first token (TTFT)\n   - **Question:** Why should these metrics be reported?\n\n2.  **Deconstruct the Metrics:**\n   - **Prompt Prefill Throughput:** How fast the model processes the input prompt (tokens per second). This is the \"read\" phase where the model attends to all prompt tokens in parallel.\n   - **Decode Throughput:** How fast the model generates output tokens (tokens per second). This is the \"write\" phase where tokens are generated autoregressively, one at a time.\n   - **Time to First Token (TTFT):** Latency from sending a prompt to receiving the first generated token. Critical for interactive/user-facing applications.\n\n3.  **Identify Core Reasons for Reporting These Metrics:**\n   - **Hardware/Software Optimization Visibility:** Different hardware (GPU, CPU, TPU, NPU) and software stacks (vLLM, llama.cpp, TensorRT-LLM, etc.) optimize differently for prefill vs. decode. Reporting",
